<taxonomicName LSID="E0BC266A-797E-5068-838F-F33A01785042" authority="Fr., Lichenogr. Europ. Reform. 435, 1831" authorityName="Fr., Lichenogr. Europ. Reform. 435" authorityYear="1831" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Verrucaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Verrucaria hochstetteri" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="hochstetteri">Verrucaria hochstetteri Fr., Lichenogr. Europ. Reform. 435, 1831</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Germania: Regni 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Würtemberg">Wuertemberg</normalizedToken>
, Blabyrae, ad rupes calcareas, Hochstetter (UPS-L-708716!, holotype).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Prothallus not seen. Thallus light grey, endolithic, dark lines between contiguous conspecific thalli present. Perithecia immersed, leaving deep pits in the rock. Involucrellum absent. Exciple 0.32-0.4 mm in diam., longer than wide, wall black, rather thin. Asci ca. 110-125 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
30-38 mm. Ascospores 0-septate, (25-)26-30(-35) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
16-20 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
The specimen is small and the description above is based on only one perithecium dissected. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fr., Lichenogr. Europ. Reform. 435" authorityYear="1831" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Verrucaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Verrucaria hochstetteri" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="hochstetteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Verrucaria hochstetteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was reported from Finland by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pykaelae, J" journalOrPublisher="Graphis Scripta" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" pagination="17 - 32" refId="B35" refString="Pykaelae, J, 2007. Additions to the lichen flora of Finland. II. Calcareous rocks and associated soils in Lohja. Graphis Scripta 19 (1): 17 - 32" title="Additions to the lichen flora of Finland. II. Calcareous rocks and associated soils in Lohja." volume="19" year="2007">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pykälä">Pykaelae</normalizedToken>
(2007)
</bibRefCitation>
. However, all the Finnish specimens have narrower spores (max. 18 mm broad) than in the type specimen of 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. hochstetteri" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="hochstetteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. hochstetteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and no dark lines between contiguous conspecific thalli. Thus, they apparently do not belong to 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. hochstetteri" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="hochstetteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. hochstetteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but to 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. foveolata" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="foveolata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. foveolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
